## 2. CSV Export Column Names — Found in Old `dataPipeline.ts` Only
These exist in old copies' `dataPipeline.ts` header maps but are **NOT in current `dataNormalization.ts`**:

| CSV Column (Exact) | Should Map To | Found In | Current Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| `Stayed to watch (%)` | `STW %` | copy 2, 3, 7 dataPipeline | ❌ Missing from HEADER_MAP |
| `Stayed to watch at 0:30 (%)` | `STW %` | copy 2, 3, 7 csvImportUtils | ❌ Missing from HEADER_MAP |
| `End screen elements shown` | (format detection only) | copy 2, 3, 7 csvImportUtils | ❌ Not mapped at all |
| `Clicks per end screen element shown (%)` | `End screen click rate` | old dataPipeline | ❌ Missing from HEADER_MAP |
| `End screen click rate` | `End screen click rate` | analyticsContract aliases | ⚠️ In contract but not HEADER_MAP |
| `Card click rate` | `Card click rate` | analyticsContract aliases | ⚠️ In contract but not HEADER_MAP |
| `annotationClickThroughRate` | `Card click rate` | old youtubeService | ⚠️ In contract aliases, not HEADER_MAP |
| `Engaged views` | `Engaged views` | copy 3, 7 dataForge | ⚠️ In contract aliases, not HEADER_MAP |
| `engagedViews` | `Engaged views` | copy 7 analyticsSelectors | ⚠️ In contract aliases, not HEADER_MAP |
| `Views from Shorts feed` | (format detection only) | copy 2, 3, 7 | ❌ Never mapped to a metric |
| `Shorts feed views` | (format detection only) | copy 2, 3, 7 | ❌ Never mapped to a metric |
| `Subscribers lost` | `Subscribers Lost` | old dataPipeline | ❌ Missing from HEADER_MAP |
| `subscribersLost` | `Subscribers Lost` | copy 3, 7 youtubeService | ❌ Missing from HEADER_MAP |

