## 3. CSV Tag / Upload Type Names
These are the `CsvTag` / `CsvUploadType` values used to classify uploaded CSVs.

### Confirmed in all versions ✅
| Tag Value | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `auto` | Auto-detect |
| `long` | Long-form video table |
| `shorts` | Shorts video table |
| `single_long_video` | Single long video CSV |
| `single_short_video` | Single short video CSV |
| `traffic` | Traffic sources table |
| `audience` | Audience demographics table |
| `geo` | Geography/country table |
| `daily` | Daily metrics chart |
| `search` | Search terms table |
| `combined` / `mixed` | Mixed/combined export |
| `external` | External traffic source |
| `other` | Unclassified |

### ❌ Missing tag — found only in older copies
| Tag Value | Meaning | Found In |
|---|---|---|
| `channel` | Channel-wide totals (not per-video) | copy 2 dataPipeline tag detection |

---

## 4. Format Detection Column Names (in `csvImportUtils.detectContentTagFromRows`)
These column names are used to sniff whether a CSV is Shorts or Long — **not mapped to metrics** but critical for correct tagging:

| Column Name | Purpose | Status |
|---|---|---|
| `Stayed to watch (%)` | Shorts signal | ✅ Present in detection logic |
| `Stayed to watch at 0:30 (%)` | Shorts signal (alt name) | ✅ Present in detection logic |
| `End screen elements shown` | Long-form signal | ✅ Present in detection logic |
| `Views from Shorts feed` | Shorts signal | ✅ Present in detection logic |
| `Shorts feed views` | Shorts signal (alt name) | ✅ Present in detection logic |
| `Average view duration` | Duration-based detection | ✅ Present in detection logic |
| `Duration` | Duration-based detection | ✅ Present in detection logic |

---

## 5. `inferTagFromPath` — Filename Keywords Used for Auto-Detection

All copies have identical path-sniffing keywords. Current `viewtube` ✅ matches.

| Keyword in filename | Detected Tag |
|---|---|
| `traffic`, `source` | `traffic` |
| `audience`, `viewer`, `subscriber` | `audience` |
| `geography`, `location`, `country` | `geo` |
| `external` | `external` |
| `search term`, `search` | `search` |
| `daily`, `date` | `daily` |
| `short` | `shorts` |
| `long`, `video` | `long` |
| `total`, `channel`, `all` | `mixed` |
| (fallback) | `other` |

---

## 6. `classifyCsvExportKind` — Export Kind Detection (copy 7 only, ✅ in current)

These column names are used to detect whether a CSV is table data, a chart export, or totals:

| Column Checked | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Video title`, `Video ID`, `video`, `Dimension` | Flags as `table_data` |
| `Date`, `Day` | Flags as `chart` |
| `Views`, `Watch Time (Hours)`, `Likes`, `Comments` | Core metrics presence check |
| `linechart`, `trend`, `time series` | Flags as `chart` |

---

## 7. API Metric Names Used in Old `youtubeService.ts` That Were Removed

These were in older `youtubeService` files and were **removed** in the current version (correctly or incorrectly):

| Old API Metric | Old Group | Correctly Removed? | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `stayedToWatch` | engagement | ✅ Yes — invalid with `dimensions=video` | CSV-only metric |
| `stayedToWatch0:30` | engagement | ✅ Yes — not a real API metric name | |
| `annotationClickThroughRate` | engagement | ✅ Yes — deprecated/removed by YouTube | Legacy annotations gone |
| `clicksPerEndScreenElementShown` | engagement | ✅ Yes — not valid API metric | CSV-only |
| `estimatedRevenuePer1000Views` | monetization | ✅ Yes — doesn't exist | Wrong name for RPM |
| `uniqueViewers` | audience_mix | ✅ Yes — not valid with `dimensions=video` | |
| `newViewers` | audience_mix | ✅ Yes — not valid with `dimensions=video` | |
| `returningViewers` | audience_mix | ✅ Yes — not valid with `dimensions=video` | |
| `casualViewers` | audience_mix | ✅ Yes — not valid with `dimensions=video` | |
| `regularViewers` | audience_mix | ✅ Yes — not valid with `dimensions=video` | |

