## 8. ⚠️ Metrics in `analyticsContract.ts` Registry With MISSING `HEADER_MAP` Entries

These metrics exist in `analyticsContract` (so they work for API responses) but have **no entry in `dataNormalization.ts` HEADER_MAP** — meaning if they appear as *CSV column headers* they will not be normalized:

| Contract Key | Label | CSV Column Name Needed in HEADER_MAP |
|---|---|---|
| `engagedViews` | Engaged views | `Engaged views`, `Engaged Views` |
| `stw` | STW % | `Stayed to watch (%)`, `Stayed to watch at 0:30 (%)` |
| `endScreenClickRate` | End screen click rate | `End screen click rate`, `Clicks per end screen element shown (%)` |
| `cardClickRate` | Card click rate | `Card click rate`, `annotationClickThroughRate` |
| `newViewers` | New Viewers | Already in HEADER_MAP ✅ |
| `returningViewers` | Returning Viewers | Already in HEADER_MAP ✅ |
| `casualViewers` | Casual viewers | Already in HEADER_MAP ✅ |
| `regularViewers` | Regular viewers | Already in HEADER_MAP ✅ |
| `uniqueViewers` | Unique viewers | Already in HEADER_MAP ✅ |
| `subscribersGained` | Subscribers Gained | Already in HEADER_MAP ✅ |

---

## 9. SUMMARY — What Needs to Be Added to `dataNormalization.ts` `HEADER_MAP`

These are the confirmed gaps. Adding them would make CSV uploads of YouTube Studio exports fully normalize into the analytics pipeline:

```typescript
// Engagement — CSV export column names not yet in HEADER_MAP
"Stayed to watch (%)": "STW %",
"Stayed to watch at 0:30 (%)": "STW %",
"Clicks per end screen element shown (%)": "End screen click rate",
"End screen click rate": "End screen click rate",
"Card click rate": "Card click rate",
"Engaged views": "Engaged views",
"Engaged Views": "Engaged views",
engagedViews: "Engaged views",
"Views from Shorts feed": "Shorts feed views",
"Shorts feed views": "Shorts feed views",
"Subscribers lost": "Subscribers Lost",
subscribersLost: "Subscribers Lost",
```
